Author: MISS G HALL
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote: This ... is new to me. I heard it for the first time used by a farming family on the Taeri Plains outside Dunedin. It means tea (i.e., the 5.30 p.m. meal) consisting of tea, bread and butter, and scones; ... a meal where nothing is cooked [and served hot].
